definitions.definition: A feudal era military-administrative officer of comital rank in the Carolingian empire and some successor states, originally in charge of a border area.
A hereditary ruling prince in certain feudal states of the Holy Roman Empire and elsewhere; the titular equivalent became known as marquis or marquess .
